title: NFL | How former Buckeyes fared | Buckeye Xtra Sports
text:
Corey Brown, WR, Carolina: Had three catches for 38 yards in a 27-16 win over Philadelphia.
Ted Ginn Jr., WR, Carolina: Had five catches for 59 yards and one carry for 43 yards in the win over Philadelphia.
Johnathan Hankins , DT, New York Giants: Had four tackles (three solo) in a 27-20 win over Dallas.
Dan Herron, RB, Buffalo: Had two carries for 9 yards in a 34-31 loss to Jacksonville.
Brian Hartline , WR, Cleveland: Had three catches for 22 yards in a 24-6 loss to St. Louis.
Cameron Heyward , DE, Pittsburgh: Had four tackles (three solo) and a sack in 23-13 loss to Kansas City.
Carlos Hyde , RB, San Francisco: Had 11 carries for 40 yards in a 20-3 loss to Seattle on Thursday.
James Laurinaitis , LB, St. Louis: Had eight tackles (four solo) in the win over Cleveland.
Malcolm Jenkins, S, Philadelphia: Had two tackles and an interception in the loss to Carolina.
Ryan Shazier , LB, Pittsburgh: Had four tackles (three solo) and a half-sack in the loss to Kansas City.
John Simon , LB, Houston: Had six tackles (four solo) in a 44-26 loss to Miami.
Devin Smith , WR, New York Jets: Had one catch for 7 yards in a 30-23 loss to New England.
Donte Whitner , S, Cleveland: Had six tackles (five solo) in the loss to St. Louis.
Others from central Ohio 
Leâ€™Veon Bell, RB, Pittsburgh: Had 17 carries for 171 yards and caught four passes for 16 yards in the loss to Kansas City.
Travis Carrie , DB, Oakland: Had three tackles (one solo) in a 37-29 win over San Diego.
Bradley McDougald, S, Tampa Bay: Had nine tackles, including six solo, in a 31-30 loss to Washington.
Mike Mitchell , S, Pittsburgh: Had six solo tackles in the loss to Kansas City.
